America Act", "last_comment_created": 1779880338739, "content": "", "score_down": 0, "author_flair_text": "", "pro_tier": 0, "is_stickied": false, "is_nsfw": false, "is_deleted": false, "is_image": true, "comments": 15, "score_up": 141, "is_edited": false, "is_moderator": false, "awards": 0, "vote_state": 2, "link_metadata": {"status": 200}, "post_flair_text": "\ud83d\udea8\u00a0\u00a0LOCK THEM UP\u00a0\u00a0\ud83d\udea8", "archive_id": ""}, {"is_locked": false, "tweet_id": "", "sticky_comment": 0, "is_video_mp4": false, "type": "link", "uuid": "1ASsdoq3ja", "is_twitter": false, "is_admin": false, "score": 40, "suggested_sort": 0, "post_flair_class": "", "id": 8642346, "raw_content": "", "author": "rdvs34283", "created": 1779877128063, "profile_picture": "p9HQtdiLq2uP", "community": "TheDonald", "ad_tier": 2, "last_comment_author": "", "is_video": false, "video_link": "", "is_new_user": false, "domain": "www.frontpagemag.com", "is_crosspost": false, "preview": "https://media.scored.co/preview/1ASsdoq3ja.png", "removal_source": "", "link": "https://www.frontpagemag.com/harvard-fakes-grade-inflation-reform/", "author_flair_class": "", "is_removed": false, "media": {"resized_resolutions": [], "blurhash": "", "full_resolution": []}, "title": "Harvard Fakes Grade Inflation Reform.\nIn 1950, the average GPA at Harvard was 2.6 out of 4. By 2003, it had risen to 3.4. In 2025, it was 3.8. Now, they'll be limiting A grades to 20% of students, with no limit on A-minuses. An A- is now the new A. ", "last_comment_created": 1779877128063, "content": "", "score_down": 0, "author_flair_text": "", "pro_tier": 0, "is_stickied": false, "is_nsfw": false, "is_deleted": false, "is_image": false, "comments": 0, "score_up": 40, "is_edited": false, "is_moderator": false, "awards": 0, "vote_state": 2, "link_metadata": {"description": "An A- is now the new A", "large_image": "fegUkSIINXWxxHNo.png", "title": "Harvard Fakes Grade Inflation Reform | Frontpage Mag"}, "post_flair_text": "", "archive_id": ""}, {"is_locked": false, "tweet_id": "", "sticky_comment": 0, "is_video_mp4": false, "type": "link", "uuid": "1ASsdnilHE", "is_twitter": false, "is_admin": false, "score": 316, "suggested_sort": 0, "post_flair_class": "", "id": 8641728, "raw_content": "", "author": "neveser", "created": 1779836668972, "profile_picture": "", "community": "TheDonald", "ad_tier": 2, "last_comment_author": "MagaJay02", "is_video": false, "video_link": "", "is_new_user": false, "domain": "media.scored.co", "is_crosspost": false, "preview": "https://media.scored.co/preview/1ASsdnilHE.png", "removal_source": "", "link": "https://media.scored.co/post/ElJ00A7dqgfV.jpeg", "author_flair_class": "", "is_removed": false, "media": {"resized_resolutions": [{"reference": "/scale/00zwRCFoGBjOviUk.jpeg", "width": 731, "content-type": "jpeg", "height": 768}], "blurhash": "UNFP4|bJ00t7D%ax%2oM00V@~VoM~XRkE2t7", "full_resolution": [1267, 1206]}, "title": "Charges dropped!!!", "last_comment_created": 1779886052262, "content": "", "score_down": 0, "author_flair_text": "", "pro_tier": 0, "is_stickied": false, "is_nsfw": false, "is_deleted": false, "is_image": true, "comments": 17, "score_up": 316, "is_edited": false, "is_moderator": false, "awards": 0, "vote_state": 2, "link_metadata": {"status": 200}, "post_flair_text": "", "archive_id": ""}, {"is_locked": false, "tweet_id": "", "sticky_comment": 0, "is_video_mp4": false, "type": "text", "uuid": "1ASsdoqbti", "is_twitter": false, "is_admin": false, "score": 25, "suggested_sort": 0, "post_flair_class": "", "id": 8642552, "raw_content": "First Round:\n\n-Cornyn ran 1st w/ 665k votes\n\n-Paxton, 2nd, 638K votes\n\n-Total Votes, 1565k votes\n\nRunoff:\n\n-Paxton, 63.9%, 880kvotes\n\n-Cornyn, 36.1%, 498k votes\n\n-Total Votes, 1378k votes\n\nDrop off was only 187k votes or about 12%.  That is pretty good turnout for a runoff.  Realize the 3rd place finisher is first round was Wesley Hunt w/ over 203k votes.  More people voted in the runoff than the total of both candidates first round votes.\n\nPaxton received 242k more votes in the runoff and Cornyn received 167k votes less.  Even if all of Hunt's voters went to Cornyn in a no drop-off scenario, that is still less than 242k.  Also have to consider the 12% drop-off in total votes.\n\nThe only way there could be that much swing is if a significant number of Cornyn voters switched in the runoff or stayed home.\n\nYou would expect Cornyn's total to decline no more than 12% based on the total vote drop-off.  He should have had a minimum of 585k votes in the runoff.   He seemed to lose approximately 87k of his original votes.\n\nWhen evaluating DJT's endorsements during this cycle if there were a way to scale the magnitude of the endorsement, this is it.  Generally, endorsements may help at the margin.  The vast majority of votes are baked in.  The only two major developments between the first round and the runoff were, SAVE Act was abandoned and the DJT endorsement.\n\nIf I were managing any candidate in any race for either side, I would do an in-depth study of this race's results.\n\nAssist goes to chatgpt in gathering the numbers.", "author": "dataonly", "created": 1779886209359, "profile_picture": "", "community": "TheDonald", "ad_tier": 2, "last_comment_author": "dataonly", "is_video": false, "video_link": "", "is_new_user": false, "domain": "", "is_crosspost": false, "preview": "", "removal_source": "", "link": "", "author_flair_class": "", "is_removed": false, "media": {"resized_resolutions": [], "blurhash": "", "full_resolution": []}, "title": "Magnitude of Paxton's Win Deserves Closer Analysis", "last_comment_created": 1779893830358, "content": "<p>First Round:</p>\n<p>-Cornyn ran 1st w/ 665k votes</p>\n<p>-Paxton, 2nd, 638K votes</p>\n<p>-Total Votes, 1565k votes</p>\n<p>Runoff:</p>\n<p>-Paxton, 63.9%, 880kvotes</p>\n<p>-Cornyn, 36.1%, 498k votes</p>\n<p>-Total Votes, 1378k votes</p>\n<p>Drop off was only 187k votes or about 12%.  That is pretty good turnout for a runoff.  Realize the 3rd place finisher is first round was Wesley Hunt w/ over 203k votes.  More people voted in the runoff than the total of both candidates first round votes.</p>\n<p>Paxton received 242k more votes in the runoff and Cornyn received 167k votes less.  Even if all of Hunt's voters went to Cornyn in a no drop-off scenario, that is still less than 242k.  Also have to consider the 12% drop-off in total votes.</p>\n<p>The only way there could be that much swing is if a significant number of Cornyn voters switched in the runoff or stayed home.</p>\n<p>You would expect Cornyn's total to decline no more than 12% based on the total vote drop-off.  He should have had a minimum of 585k votes in the runoff.   He seemed to lose approximately 87k of his original votes.</p>\n<p>When evaluating DJT's endorsements during this cycle if there were a way to scale the magnitude of the endorsement, this is it.  Generally, endorsements may help at the margin.  The vast majority of votes are baked in.  The only two major developments between the first round and the runoff were, SAVE Act was abandoned and the DJT endorsement.</p>\n<p>If I were managing any candidate in any race for either side, I would do an in-depth study of this race's results.</p>\n<p>Assist goes to chatgpt in gathering the numbers.</p>\n", "score_down": 0, "author_flair_text": "", "pro_tier": 0, "is_stickied": false, "is_nsfw": false, "is_deleted": false, "is_image": false, "comments": 3, "score_up": 25, "is_edited": true, "is_moderator": false, "awards": 0, "vote_state": 2, "link_metadata": {"status": 200}, "post_flair_text": "", "archive_id": ""}, {"is_locked": false, "tweet_id": "", "sticky_comment": 0, "is_video_mp4": false, "type": "link", "uuid": "1ASsdnj2ak", "is_twitter": false, "is_admin": false, "score": 238, "suggested_sort": 0, "post_flair_class": "", "id": 8641866, "raw_content": "", "author": "ncswicn", "created": 1779842133840, "profile_picture": "vA8wUXPLp01X", "community": "TheD